other_tests.findings: The heart is enlarged. The liver demonstrates homogeneous attenuation throughout. No evidence of focal lesions in the liver. Small amount of free fluid noted. The gallbladder is surgically absent. The pancreas shows normal attenuation without focal lesions. No pancreatic ductal dilatation or peripancreatic stranding observed. Spleen normal. Kidneys are normal and symmetric with punctate renal hilar calcifications noted. Extensive diverticulosis in small bowel. Reproductive organs show calcified fibroids. No significant lymphadenopathy. Moderate atherosclerotic disease noted.
